{
  "texts": [
    "It is possible that important information might have been missing, or inaccurately reported, in the clinician-generated discharge summaries as well.",
    "In this cross-sectional study of 100 ED encounters, we found that LLMs could generate accurate discharge summaries, but were liable to hallucination and omission of clinically relevant information.",
    "Our results suggest that the location of errors within a GPT-generated discharge summary may vary based on the type of error.",
    "A comprehensive understanding of where errors are most likely to occur in GPT-generated clinical text is critically important to facilitate 324 clinician review and revision of such content and prevent patient harm. 325 Table 2.",
    "Manual categorization of expert reviewer comments providing further details for each error subtype among GPT-4-generated discharge summaries compared to the ground-truth, original Emergency Medicine provider note."
  ]
}